</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-30_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-31_ pf-text-1"><strong>First aid</strong> - Immediate assistance provided to a person suffering from a minor or severe illness or injury, with care provided to preserve life, prevent the condition from worsening, or promote recovery.




























</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-33_ pf-text-1"><strong>First aider </strong>- A person trained in first aid techniques and can administer care until professional medical help arrives competently.



























