</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-39_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Schools in the UK are legally required to ensure the safety and health of their pupils. This responsibility is supported by several pieces of legislation:















</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-41_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-42_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety (First-Aid) Regulations 1981</strong> - This regulation requires all educational institutions to have appropriate first-aid equipment, facilities, and personnel trained in first aid.





























</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-44_ pf-text-1"><strong>The Education (Independent School Standards) Regulations 2014 </strong>- Schools must actively safeguard and promote children's welfare, including providing adequate first aid training and facilities.




























</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-46_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-47_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-48_ pf-heading-1-h3">Best practices
</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-50_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Best school practice first aid training involves:
















</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-52_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-53_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regular training </strong>- Conducting first aid training sessions bi-annually for staff to handle emergencies effectively.





























</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-55_ pf-text-1"><strong>Student training</strong> - Integrating basic first aid lessons into the school curriculum to foster a culture of safety and preparedness.




























