</h3><p class="sc-kHOZwM oQMan pf-69_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To effectively implement first aid training in schools, it's essential to:
















</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-71_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-72_ pf-text-1"><strong>Identify requirements</strong> - Assess the specific first aid needs of the school based on student activities and school size.


























</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-74_ pf-text-1"><strong>Choose qualified trainers</strong> - Partner with accredited organisations like the Red Cross or St John Ambulance for training sessions.


























</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah hUMvDY pf-76_ pf-text-1"><strong>Customise training modules</strong> - Tailor training sessions to address the most common injuries and health issues that might occur in school settings.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-iqseJM ducrfW pf-78_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-79_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-bTfYFJ fFWOZc pf-80_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
